source: hi all ,   in the latest rc7 , there is a surprising update regarding the header : phofurl  all headers are now lowercased .  argument for this modification is ieftf 's http/ verid40 1.1 verid0 specifications .   as far i understand , header case-insensitive support is a server side concerns , not client side .  it is stated `` field names are case-insensitive . `` , making server more tolerant .  it is not stated `` headers sent by the client should be lowercased '' , making client library deciding what to do with your header .   this change is a breaking one .  consequence are immediate by broken server-side compatibility .  for exemple , a server-side expected `` authorization '' header , which is now lowercased by client in `` authorization '' , is not recognised anymore by the server .   thank you for your support .
title_1: headers are now lowercased in the latest rc7
title_2: all headers are now lowercased in client side
